The Economist was founded as a print newspaper in 1843, but today we have a growing digital operation and 50m followers on our social media accounts. Ever more people are encountering our journalism for the first time on Instagram, Facebook, Twitter or LinkedIn. The social media team comprises creative and enterprising journalists, some of whom join us on one-year fellowships to help shape The Economist’s digital future. We are now recruiting a new fellow to join us in London.  This position is with our Stories team, which manages our Instagram account and is tasked with bringing the best of our journalism to life visually across all social platforms. The successful candidate will have strong illustration and animation skills, and a track record of clearly and concisely distilling complicated topics into social-friendly content. A strong grasp of, and commitment to, our design standards is essential. The position would suit a graduate with experience in creating content for mobile platforms and designing for the web and digital. Editorial or journalistic experience is highly desirable, as is a proven ability to work to tight deadlines. Essential skills Requirements If this sounds like you, send the following items to edsocialjob@economist.com: Successful candidates will be hired on one-year contracts and paid £2,000 per month. The deadline for applications is Sunday September 8th. Applicants must be eligible to work in the UK. Start dates are flexible. The Economist Group values diversity. We are committed to equal opportunities and creating an inclusive environment for all our employees. We welcome applicants regardless of ethnic origin, national origin, gender, race, colour, religious beliefs, disability, sexual orientation or age.